Hill, LC 65-19851.\n* Sauerlander, Willibald. ''The Catholic Rubens: Saints and Martyrs'' (Getty Research Institute; 2014); 311 pages; looks at his altarpieces in the context of the Counter-Reformation.\n* Schrader, Stephanie, ''[http://shop.getty.edu/products/looking-east-rubenss-encounter-with-asia-978-1606061312 Looking East: Ruben's Encounter with Asia]'', Getty Publications, Los Angeles, 2013. {{ISBN|978-1-60606-131-2}}\n* Vlieghe, Hans, ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=AS_NXFoY0M4C&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false Flemish Art and Architecture 1585\u20131700]'', Yale University Press, Pelican History of Art, New Haven and London, 1998. {{ISBN|0-300-07038-1}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Peter Paul Rubens}}\n{{Wikiquote|Peter Paul Rubens}}\n* {{Art UK bio}}\n* {{Britannica|511894}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100720205533/http://www.rubenshuis.be/eCache/MCE/30/05/169.html ''Rubenshuis''] in [[Antwerp]], ([[Belgium]]) is the former house of Rubens, now converted into a museum\n* [http://rubenianum.digipolisweb.be/en/pagina/corpus-rubenianum-ludwig-burchard-online Corpus Rubenianum Ludwig Burchard Online]\n* [http://www.lalaragimov.com/research Rubens's palette and painting materials, with bibliography]\n* [https://www.theguardian.com/arts/features/story/0,11710,903646,00.html ''The Guardian'': Rubens]\n* [http://www.peterpaulrubens.org/ 290 of images by the artist, and more]\n* [http://emlo.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/blog/?catalogue=peter-paul-rubens The Correspondence of Peter Paul Rubens] in [http://emlo.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/home EMLO]\n* [http://balat.kikirpa.be/pi/364 Peter Paul Rubens on BALaT \u2013 Belgian Art Links and Tools (KIK-IRPA, Brussels)]\n\n{{Paintings by Rubens}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rubens, Peter Paul}}\n[[Category:Peter Paul Rubens| ]]\n[[Category:1577 births]]\n[[Category:1640 deaths]]\n[[Category:16th-century Belgian people]]\n[[Category:16th-century Flemish painters]]\n[[C